name: Balance bike
description: A balance bike is a pedal-less bike with two wheels.

name: Scooter
description: Scooter a child's vehicle that typically has two wheels with a low footboard between them, is steered by a handlebar, and is propelled by pushing one foot against the ground while resting the other on the footboard.

name: Tricycle
description: A tricycle, often abbreviated to trike, is a human-powered (or gravity-powered) three-wheeled vehicle.

name: Bike with stabilizers
description: Training wheels  are an additional wheel or wheels mounted parallel to the rear wheel of a bicycle that assist learners until they have developed a usable sense of balance on the bicycle.
